**Waves **could be generated / controlled many ways. **Two major categories**:
**1. **you could make THE SIMULATION ITSELF generate "wave like" structures - so the output material receives an already "wavy" surface. (Sim params could be controlled via the Preset Manager - NOISES are key!) A good example for this is: Tutorial Level 10B: https://youtu.be/JNlGcKN-BN8?t=57
**2. **lately (now, that we have world space features) I have been using the sim only for generating local ripples around the interacting agents --- and the large, generic wave patterns convering the whole area are generated IN THE OUTPUT MATERIAL (using the TilePattern Param Group). Usecase Levels 14-A,B,C are good examples for this: https://youtu.be/UbhPiT_bRR0?t=10
